                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>recd <persName>Samuels</persName> Translation, and I like\n                                        yours<lb/> better as the language is more eupho<add>?</add>\n                                        and<lb/> smoother than his. I cannot tell of course how<lb/>\n                                        the original is but should judge it to be a close<lb/>\n                                        translation from its resemblance in many particulars<lb/> to\n                                        the one by <persName>Samuels</persName>. I am sure the\n                                        public<lb/> would rather have Jerusalem than 3 Nos of the\n                                        Occident<lb/>—When are we to have the <date>Apl</date>\n                                        No.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Do you think you acted prudently in publishing<lb/>\n                                        <persName>Mr Poznanski's</persName> letter. I have heard but\n                                                  <hi rend=\"underline\">one</hi><lb/> opinion about\n                                        it here, which is unfavorable.<lb/> I hope it will not\n                                        injure you, and I <sic>dont</sic><lb/> see how it will\n                                        benefit you, I only write this to<lb/> let your public\n                                        opinion in this quarter.</p>\n                              <p>I have heard it remarked that <persName>Mr Leeser</persName><lb/>\n                                        denounced <persName>Dr Raphael</persName> for giving\n                                                  <sic>recommendary</sic><lb/> letters to\n                                                  <persName>Rubenstein</persName> for KKBE, and<lb/>\n                                        <persName>Mr Leeser</persName> has done the same thing himself<lb/>\n                                        <persName>Mr Moise</persName> told me that the <add>?</add>\n                                        of KKBE<lb/> have a letter from you speaking in the\n                                        highest<lb/> terms of a <persName>Mr Myer</persName> or\n                                                  <persName>Mayers</persName>, formerly<lb/> a pupil\n                                        of <persName>Dr Lennialhas<add>?</add></persName>. Write me\n                                        if it is<lb/> so—and if you know any thing of <persName>Mr\n                                                  Myers</persName><lb/> principles. I understand\n                                        that he has written to the<lb/> Trustees that he believes\n                                        and approves of the bible<lb/>\n                                        <hi rend=\"underline\">subject however to criticism</hi>, I\n                                        also learn<lb/> that <persName>Poznanski</persName> has\n                                        written to <persName>Mr Myer</persName> that he<lb/>\n                                        <hi rend=\"underline\">rejoices</hi> in his principles—there\n                                        was to be a<lb/> meeting last night, on the subject, and</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p32f7kb46/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
